kristin gazlay who has been a reporter editor 
and bureau chief for the associated press is the aps new 
assistant managing editor for features 
her appointment was announced monday by ap president louis d 
boccardi 
ms gazlay 32 has been the aps special projects editor in new 
york since january in that post she has worked closely wth the 
assistant managing editor for features on planning production and 
editing of aps national enterprise report 
before her new york appointment ms gazlay was chief of bureau 
in little rock where she directed ap operations for arkansas she 
joined the ap in dallas in 1980 and was named correspondent in san 
antonio in 1983 
in 1984 ms gazlay was named news editor for texas and she 
became assistant chief of bureau in dallas later that year 
ms gazlay a graduate of southern methodist university 
succeeds julia dunlap who resigned to join the oregonian in 
portland ore 
