<TEXT>
the world war ii allies that carved up nazi 
germany will meet this week to discuss polands fear that a unified 
german state may try to take back some of its old lands 
foreign ministers from the germanys and the united states 
soviet union france and britain are to meet in bonn on saturday to 
discuss the global implications of german unification 
a team of experts from the six nations held preliminary 
discussions monday night to prepare an agenda for the historic 
talks 
after meeting for six hours at a secluded guest house near a 
castle north of east berlin the officials issued a brief statement 
saying polands borders would be discussed at the saturday session 
ultraconservatives in west germany say a united germany would 
have a valid claim to large sections of nazi germany that were 
ceded to poland to make up for a larger section of poland absorbed 
by the soviet union after the war 
chancellor helmut kohl of west germany caused a furor earlier 
this year when he refused for several months to state unequivocally 
that a united germany would recognize polands existing borders 
he later said he would recognize the boundaries 
poland will be allowed to participate in the sixnation talks 
when its lands are discussed 
the greater issue in the international talks the role of a 
united germany in the superpower alliances is to be discussed at 
future negotiations involving the six nations alone 
moscow worried about disrupting the current european balance of 
power to its disadvantage has rejected the wests position that a 
united germany must be a nato member 
soviet foreign minister eduard shevardnadze secretary of state 
james a baker iii and west german foreign minister hansdietrich 
genscher were to hold informal talks friday in advance of 
saturdays meeting 
soviet officials have indicated that they want a united germany 
to be military nonaligned with joint membership in both the 
warsaw pact and the north atlantic treaty organization 
east germany has said it is willing to agree to temporary nato 
membership if the alliance undergoes fundamental changes to reflect 
the eastwest thaw 
east germany is now in the sovietled alliance and west germany 
is in nato 
kohl tried to ease soviet objections on monday 
he said in a statement that he is certain that we will come to 
a reasonable agreement also with the soviet union on the matter 
of a united germanys strategic allegiances 
kohl added that west germany is ready for a comprehensive 
cooperation with the soviet union in the areas of economy 
technological exchanges athletic meetings and cooperation in 
security questions 
the statement did not elaborate on any of the points 
the two germanys meanwhile are holding separate talks on the 
domestic aspects of reunification they plan to merge their 
economies and social institutions by july 2 
delegations from both countries held more negotiations in bonn 
on monday and hoped to complete a final plan during meetings 
thursday and friday in berlin 
crucial differences still separate the germanys 
west germany has said it will trade most east german marks at a 
1to1 exchange but wants to trade personal savings accounts of 
more 2300 at a 2to1 rate 
east germany is demanding a higher ceiling and also wants to 
temporarily retain subsidies for housing energy and public 
services 
the two sets of talks on german unification likely will produce 
several agreements that will lay a foundation for unification but 
a full political merger between the germanys is not expected to be 
completed until next year 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

