eastern europe quietly celebrated its 
liberation from decades of communist ritual on may day 
substituting music festivals and picnics for the proletarian 
parades of the past 
in moscow a brief burst of the popular rage that swept 
communist leaders from power across eastern europe erupted in red 
square where the traditional parade was open to all for the first 
time in decades 
columns of demonstrators taunted soviet president mikhail s 
gorbachev and other top leaders with cries of shame they 
