today 
watkins told a senate armed services subcommittee that four 
plants including three reactors at its savannah river complex in 
south carolina will resume producing nuclear weapons components by 
the end of 1991 
the three reactors have been shut down since mid1988 over 
environmental and safetyrelated concerns us nuclear weapons 
production has ground to a halt in the past several months because 
of that and suspension of operations at the rocky flats plant in 
colorado last november over similar concerns 
watkins said the k reactor at savannah river is tentatively 
scheduled to reopen with lowpower testing on dec 10 followed by 
fullpower production in late december or early january 
the p reactor at savannah river is to be restarted next march 
with production of weapons components scheduled to resume in april 
he said 
the l reactor at savannah river will be restarted in september 
1991 watkins said 
in addition he said two facilities at the rocky flats plant for 
producing the plutonium triggers in atomic warheads will resume 
operations in june and july 
