naknek said she didnt feel the quake even though the epicenter 
was 25 miles away 
there have been no damage reports she said people have 
been calling to say they were shook up that their chandeliers were 
swaying but theres nothing 10 miles south of king salmon but 
tundra 
the richter scale is a gauge of the energy released by an 
earthquake as measured by the ground motion recorded on a 
seismograph 
every increase of one number means that the ground motion is 10 
times greater 
an earthquake of 35 on the richter scale can cause slight 
damage in the local area 4 moderate damage 5 considerable damage 
6 severe damage 
