tellers refused to wear bank uniforms instead donning tshirts and 
slacks to press their demand for freer labor activity 
the capitals subway workers declared a twoday protest 
refusing to sell tickets and giving passengers free rides 
in southern chonju dozens of radical students armed with steel 
pipes and firebombs attacked a building where government party 
officials were to meet and smashed windows said yonhap the south 
korean news agency 
