<TEXT>
george h beebe whose decadeslong career helped 
guide the miami herald to a position of prominence and developed 
its role in coverage of latin america has died of cancer he was 
80 
beebe died monday at the miami heart institute 
the herald became a recognized chronicler of latin america while 
beebe served as managing editor some of the reporters he hired 
became pulitzer prize winners and knightridder executives 
beebe joined the herald as a copy editor in 1944 served as 
managing editor in 19511966 then was senior managing editor until 
1972 when he became an associate publisher and continued 
contributing travel articles 
beebe helped found the world press freedom committee in 1976 and 
served as its executive director and chairman of the 
anticensorship alliance of 32 journalistic organizations he also 
served as president of the inter american press association 
george beebe ran the news department the way he lived his life 
a caring compassionate person who believed in letting the reader 
feel he was important said lee hills managing editor when beebe 
arrived at the herald and retired chairman of its parent 
knightridder group 
the pittsfield mass native was managing editor of the boston 
university news for 13 years before joining the herald 
beebe prepared his own obituary for the newspaper writing if 
i have been successful it is because i have had helen at my side 
she has been a patient understanding and devoted newspaper wife 
he is survived by his wife three nieces and four nephews 
a memorial service is planned thursday at the first united 
methodist church of coral gables 
</TEXT>
