about 10500 soviet jews arrived in israel in 
april the largest monthly figure since the start of a mass soviet 
immigration to the jewish state last year an official said tuesday 
it was the first time israel published a figure for soviet 
arrivals since early march when such statistics were censored in 
response to arab guerrilla threats to attack immigrants 
gad ben ari the spokesman for the quasigovernmental jewish 
agency which is partly responsible for resettling the immigrants 
said 10500 arrived in april he added israels goal is to bring 
the maximum amount of people in the minimum amount of time 
before april the monthly immigration figure for soviet jews was 
between 4000 and 6000 israeli and foreign reports said in 1989 
12000 soviets settled in israel and in 1988 only 2000 arrived 
the relaxation in the censorship of immigration statistics 
appears to be a result of pressure from overseas fundraisers 
particularly those in the united states fundraisers say they need 
the immigration figures in their drives to raise money to absorb 
the newcomers 
israeli officials estimate up to 300000 soviet jews will 
emigrate to israel in the next few years the influx comes because 
of a loosening of immigration procedures in the soviet union and 
tighter restrictions on us immigration 
