friends not only do they support our independence initiatives but 
they also want to cooperate with us in practical terms because they 
receive many of their food supplies from us 
mrs prunskiene is in canada as part of a north american swing 
to ask for more economic ties with her republic she is to meet 
thursday with president bush at the white house 
lithuania has struggled for two weeks since the soviets cut 
supplies of fuel medicine and other goods following lithuanias 
march 11 declaration of independence 
the kremlin does not recognize the declaration saying lithuania 
must follow soviet law on secession 
lithuania was forcibly incorporated into the soviet union in 
1940 
