current law aimed at protecting endangered sea 
turtles could cause widespread embargoes of imported shrimp next 
year a bush administration official told congress tuesday 
the law approved last year forbidding shrimp imports after 1991 
from countries that are lax about turtle protection may be 
unrealistic said edward e wolfe deputy assistant secretary of 
state for oceans and fisheries affairs 
there is little chance that these countries will be able to 
meet the standards required by the law in the time allowed no 
