without an extension of the may 1 1991 deadline requiring foreign 
countries to be as tough on shrimpers as the united states 
panama honduras guatemala and costa rica are sure to be 
affected by such an embargo wolfe said 
it has long been the bipartisan policy of the united states 
to support efforts aimed at promoting economic development and 
political stability in central america he said 
now when the region will be looking more than ever to the 
united states to support its democratic efforts we are preparing 
to impose trade sanctions totaling more than 115 million for these 
four countries alone 
