<TEXT>
the lawyers committee for human rights said 
tuesday that 68 legal professionals were murdered worldwide in 1989 
and at least 209 others were tortured detained or harassed because 
they advocated justice 
the lawyers and judges with whom this report is concerned 
stand as symbols of the struggle for justice and human rights 
said committee chairman marvin e frankel 
the report chronicled abuses against lawyers judges law 
students and law professors in 48 countries 
it did not include iraq saudi arabia albania north korea and 
other countries where lawyers and judges do not or cannot challenge 
abuses committed by governments or security forces the committee 
said 
the lawyers committee for human rights is a 12yearold 
organization based in new york its data was gathered by a 
worldwide network of lawyers which shares information and appeals 
to authorities in certain cases 
colombia headed the list with 58 abuses onefourth of the total 
cases reported 
the committee said the abuses included the killings of 17 
lawyers and 10 judges in 1989 more than 225 judges magistrates 
and court workers have been murdered since 1980 in colombia where 
political and drugrelated violence is commonplace 
in countries like brazil colombia el salvador the 
philippines and sri lanka among others the threats to the due 
process of law and to the professionals devoted to administering 
the process come from a frightening array of diverse forces the 
report said 
twelve legal professionals were killed in peru last year 
including marcial capelleti cisneros a professor and former 
president of the committee for the defense of human rights 
cisneros was murdered may 29 while giving a test to law students at 
the university of huamanga 
the report cited 25 cases of detention torture and harassment 
in israel mostly involving palestinian lawyers who represented 
detainees in the occupied west bank and gaza strip 
in china seven lawyers and law students were detained xiong 
yan a law student who met with premier li peng to discuss student 
demands during the prodemocracy demonstration in tiananmen square 
was arrested june 14 and charged with organizing and inciting a 
counterrevolutionary rebellion 
