<TEXT>
fifty years ago hitlers blitzkrieg overran 
belgium the netherlands and france now they are partners of 
germany but cautious about the prospect of a unified powerhouse 
next door 
the french whose maginot line could not stop the germans now 
lead an effort to guarantee them a central role in a singlemarket 
western europe 
french belgian and dutch officials say the closer the ties the 
better suggesting a nonaligned germany would cause greater 
concern 
i have always believed the arbitrary division of germany was 
senseless said foreign minister roland dumas of france but 
the situation inherited from the war cannot be improved without the 
participation of other countries 
west germany is the largest trading partner of all three 
countries conquered by german forces in a sixweek onslaught that 
began may 10 1940 its relationship with france is particularly 
close encompassing everything from military cooperation to 
cultural television programming 
frenchgerman friendship is more alive than ever president 
francois mitterrand once a german prisoner of war said at the end 
of a harmonious twoday summit in late april with chancellor helmut 
kohl 
in normandy which was devastated by the battles that followed 
the allied invasion of june 1944 dozens of towns have established 
twin city relationships with german municipalities 
stateowned aerospatiale of france recently began a joint 
helicopter production project with messerschmittboelkowblohm 
which made many of hitlers warplanes 
among the most vivid symbols of frenchgerman reconciliation is 
a joint army brigade 2100 soldiers from each country being 
deployed in west germany 
brigade officers have overcome language difficulties and even a 
potential wardrobe dispute the men will wear frenchstyle blue 
berets but tilt them to the right in accordance with german custom 
klaus becher and ingo kolboom of the research institute of the 
german society for foreign policy have proposed stationing 
additional frenchgerman brigades in east germany after 
unification to replace soviet troops 
the frenchgerman relationship dates to a treaty signed in 1963 
by president charles de gaulle and chancellor konrad adenauer the 
governments have closer and more systematic consultation on 
political military and economic matters than any other two in 
western europe 
polls indicate the french and germans consider each other their 
closest foreign friends kohl and mitterrand embodied this 
sentiment in 1984 when they joined hands at verdun the world war i 
battle site in dedicating a plaque consecrating the reconciliation 
of france and germany 
there appear to be few plans for marking the 50th anniversary of 
the german entry into paris june 14 or the french surrender june 
22 
the french dont like to celebrate defeat said dominique 
moisi associate director of the french institute of foreign 
relations he suggested the french would focus on de gaulle who on 
june 18 1940 made his first radio appeal from england to his 
countrymen to resist the occupation 
moisi said in an interview that fear of a powerful united 
germany is based more on the french lack of confidence in their 
ability to compete than mistrust of germany 
political analyst pierre lellouche wrote in le point magazine 
in paris where they officially pretend to rejoice at german 
unity they worry in private about its consequences 
some french officials anticipate the development of a german 
superpower that would reduce france to a secondary role he 
said 
wolfgang bergsdorf a kohl adviser cited a poll recently 
indicating 68 percent of french people favored german unification 
unhappily the politicians in france in contrast to the 
general population are reticent now that german unity has become 
more than a sacred wish bergsdorf said 
the belgian and dutch economies are even more intertwined with 
west germany than the french the dutch guilder exchange rate 
closely follows the deutschmark and hollands interest rates are 
virtually based on the west german central banks prime rate 
queen beatrix and her mother juliana are married to germans 
both husbands gained acceptance by learning dutch and trying to 
understand the country but the dutch tend to view germans as 
arrogant and authoritarian 
resentment of the wartime occupation is largely responsible and 
german tourists who assume everyone speaks their language and 
accepts their currency reinforce the attitude 
shopkeepers in the border city of enschede asked west germans to 
stay away may 5 the anniversary of liberation from the nazis 
we dont think its appropriate to be confronted with germans 
then especially for older people who have been through the war 
a spokesman ba sassen told the amsterdam newspaper de telegraaf 
hollands european cup soccer victory over west germany in 1988 
inspired much antigerman emotion teenagers born decades after 
the war took to the streets chanting how the krauts are silent 
and revenge at last 
a reporter asked a dutch official at a european economic 
community meeting in december why his delegation seemed reluctant 
to mention world war ii 
we have certainly not forgotten the war he said but you 
must understand that with germany being a major partner we cannot 
say these things publicly so we let the russians say them 
</TEXT>
