<TEXT>
the bank of japan announced a major restructuring 
tuesday aimed at strengthening the central banks monetary 
operations and its ability to monitor financial institutions at 
home and abroad 
the reorganization which goes into effect on may 28 will 
reduce the number of departments at the central bank from 18 to 16 
the reorganization is designed to help the bank of japan better 
cope with the continued globalization of financial markets 
the central bank said it will set up a market operations 
division to monitor both money and capital markets and to execute 
daily monetary operations in a comprehensive manner 
the central bank said two divisions the bank relations 
division and the capital markets division will oversee the 
activities of financial institutions both at home and abroad in 
their daily monitoring of banks and securities houses 
respectively 
in addition the central bank said a new financial and payment 
system department will be set up to cope with the increased risks 
to the financial system posed by the trends toward financial 
deregulation globalization and computerization 
a new international department will combine the current foreign 
department with the overseas research function of the research and 
statistics department 
to expand the central banks international network the hong 
kong office will be made the bank of japans third chief 
representative office serving asia and oceania joining new york 
for north and south america and london for europe africa and the 
middle east 
another representative office will be added to washington dc 
bringing the number of representative offices to six 
</TEXT>
