if it decides to put itself up for sale union texas petroleum 
said it does not expect the sale to be completed before november 
a sale could mean lost jobs for many of the companys 1900 
employees including 900 in houston if a major oil company buys it 
and consolidates operations or if union texas petroleum assets are 
sold separately 
