farmers deals only with subsidies for exports and not with costly 
domestic price supports french agriculture minister henri nallet 
complained 
the 12 nations of the european community want to negotiate on 
all kinds of support to farmers nallet said tuesday 
subsidies on farm products cost taxpayers and consumers tens of 
billions of dollars a year not only in the united states and europe 
but in many other countries governments generally agree they 
should be reduced but the ec rejects the us goal of eliminating 
them completely 
nearly 100 governments taking part in the uruguay round of 
trade talks are trying to get agreements by the end of the year on 
many kinds of trade subsidizing farmers is a key issue 
i dont think that even in 10 or 20 years or even when were 
all dead that well be able to come to the point where theres no 
assistance given to farmers whatsoever nallet told reporters 
after a day of talks with us leaders 
he said us agriculture secretary clayton yeutter showed him an 
interesting plan for what is called tariffication under it 
many kinds of subsidies and other barriers to trade would be 
converted into a single barrier customs duties on imported farm 
products 
once governments agreed on such a conversion it would be 
simpler to reduce the barriers 
we can agree on tariffication as long as all subsidies are 
included nallet said the american plan would deal only with 
export subsidies not with domestic price supports 
he praised the work of the organization for economic and 
cooperation and development which groups the governments of the 
major industrial countries in calculating the value of their farm 
subsidies it showed new zealand giving the lowest subsidies 
amounting to only about 10 percent of its products value 
australias subsidies are only a little greater he said 
